<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><strong>On Norway’s mainland coast in Trøms county, north of the Arctic Circle and close to the Swedish border, the harbour town of Narvik is surrounded by stunning natural scenery, including the ‘Skjomtind’ mountain, named ‘The Sleeping Queen’ after Queen Victoria! Narvik is also home to 6,000 year old rock carvings, a vibrant shopping area, and several museums documenting the town’s turbulent history.</strong></p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2 class="geolocation-title location-text">What's included</h2>
<ul>
<li>Direct non-stop return flights from Gatwick to Evenes</li>
<li>Return coach transfers to &amp; from Narvik</li>
<li>3 or 4 nights’ 4-star half-board hotel</li>
<li>‘Welcome Walk’ tour of Narvik</li>
<li>Evening excursion ‘In Search of the Northern Lights’</li>
<li>Day-trip on the picturesque ‘Polar Express’ railway across the Swedish border, with husky-sledding included</li>
<li>Visit to the ‘Polar Wildlife Park’ to see foxes, wolves and other Arctic wildlife</li>
<li>Buffet lunch on excursion days</li>
</ul>
PLUS ON THE 4-NIGHT BREAK:
<ul>
<li>Scenic Tour of Narvik, including trip to Narvik mountain for skiing and toboganning and visit to the War Museum</li>
<li>Traditional Sami farewell dinner</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2 class="geolocation-title location-text">YOUR CHOICE OF HOTELS</h2>
<p><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/79ea0382d4fe4481912b0f596b84ed3e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/79ea0382d4fe4481912b0f596b84ed3e}" title="Quality Hotel Narvik">Quality Hotel Narvik</a> 4 Star</strong><br />In the heart of Narvik, with easy access to the town’s attractions including the Ofoten Museum, railway and War Memorial. The modern, well furnished rooms all have bath or shower &amp; wc, TV, minibar, kettle and free Wi-Fi. <br />Code: NONA101 Single room supplement £39 per night. Supplements may apply for some activities at Polar Park - please ask for details.<br /><br /><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/a8c65f325a7d49c982f8a12e94f4160e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a8c65f325a7d49c982f8a12e94f4160e}" title="Hotel Scandic">Hotel Scandic</a> 4 Star </strong><br />The central Hotel Scandic is Narvik’s newest, with its rooftop ‘Tøtta’ bar and restaurant, and super views over Narvik, the fjord and surrounding mountains. The spacious bedrooms all have bath or shower &amp; wc, TV, minifridge, and free Wi-Fi. <br />Code: NONA102 Single room supplement £39 per night. Supplements may apply for some activities at Polar Park - please ask for details.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow" style="text-align: center;">
<h2>Prices for your choice of either <a data-udi="umb://document/79ea0382d4fe4481912b0f596b84ed3e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/79ea0382d4fe4481912b0f596b84ed3e}" title="Quality Hotel Narvik">Quality Hotel</a> or <a data-udi="umb://document/a8c65f325a7d49c982f8a12e94f4160e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a8c65f325a7d49c982f8a12e94f4160e}" title="Hotel Scandic">Hotel Scandic</a></h2>
<p>3 nights Feb 28 Mar 6,13 <strong>£799 </strong><br />4 nights Mar 2, 9 <strong>£899</strong></p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow" style="text-align: center;">
